                            <comment id="15144623" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 12 Feb 2016 14:21:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was able to reproduce the problem by running the existing unit test with &lt;tt&gt;-Duser.language=fr -Duser.country=FR&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master in commits d86a215 and 6216d98.&lt;br/&gt;
Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15146503" author="lhochet" created="Sun, 14 Feb 2016 11:28:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, those tests are passing now.&lt;br/&gt;
I wonder if FixedFormat.getLength() and FixedFormat.getDatePatternLength() shouldn&apos;t be annotated to return inaccurate results for formats with short months.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
